01:12.600 --> 01:13.666
There he is.

01:13.667 --> 01:15.946
All hail the birthday boy.

01:15.970 --> 01:17.237
[popper bangs]

01:17.238 --> 01:18.538
Oh, what the hell was that?

01:18.539 --> 01:19.939
Charles, probably shouldn't
have done that

01:19.940 --> 01:21.141
in a police station.

01:21.142 --> 01:22.675
And not celebrate
your birthday properly?

01:22.676 --> 01:23.709
I'd rather get shot.

01:23.744 --> 01:24.878
You do you, Boyle.

01:24.879 --> 01:26.045
I'm doing me.

01:26.080 --> 01:27.080
What's this case?

01:27.081 --> 01:28.615
Oh, this isn't work.

01:28.616 --> 01:30.884
It's research on your mom
since we're finally meeting.

01:30.885 --> 01:32.318
It's very thorough.

01:32.319 --> 01:34.187
Just relax.
She's gonna love you.

01:34.188 --> 01:35.789
You're both strong,
accomplished women

01:35.790 --> 01:37.157
that have seen me naked.

01:37.158 --> 01:39.259
I used to be so good
at meeting grownups.

01:39.260 --> 01:41.528
I'd just sing
"Itsy Bitsy Spider" flawlessly

01:41.529 --> 01:43.930
and ride that wave
till bath time.

01:43.931 --> 01:46.398
But now...
it's anybody's guess.

01:46.434 --> 01:48.768
All right, what I am about
to say will make you very horny,

01:48.769 --> 01:51.538
but you have to try and remember
that we're still at work.

01:51.539 --> 01:52.939
Do you want me to quiz you?

01:52.940 --> 01:54.339
Oh, God, yes.

01:54.375 --> 01:56.076
Wow.
Okay, great.

01:56.077 --> 01:57.776
What is my mother's favorite
drink?

01:57.812 --> 01:58.911
Red wine over ice.

01:58.946 --> 02:01.181
Just like Diane Keaton,
or so she always says.

02:01.182 --> 02:02.614
Favorite topics of conversation?

02:02.650 --> 02:04.017
Jimmy Carter was underrated,

02:04.018 --> 02:05.985
how beautiful
some front doors are.

02:05.986 --> 02:07.320
What's Jane Seymour up to?

02:07.321 --> 02:08.721
And how cool is it

02:08.722 --> 02:10.356
that the ladies across
the street are lesbians?

02:10.357 --> 02:11.658
Great.
Nice work.

02:11.659 --> 02:14.260
Topics to avoid: how my dad
left us and ruined our lives,

02:14.261 --> 02:16.396
how my dad got remarried twice
and ruined our lives,

02:16.397 --> 02:17.664
how my dad moved to Canada

02:17.665 --> 02:18.964
- and ruined our lives.
- You know what?

02:18.999 --> 02:20.879
I'm just gonna steer clear
of your dad entirely.

02:20.901 --> 02:21.901
Smart.

02:21.902 --> 02:23.236
You're gonna be fine, all right?

02:23.237 --> 02:26.106
She's gonna totally love you.

02:26.107 --> 02:27.941
Are those her dental records?

02:27.942 --> 02:30.143
Gina, are you excited for our

02:30.144 --> 02:32.378
"Escape the Room"
team-building exercise?

02:32.379 --> 02:34.581
I told you, sir,
it would be far more effective

02:34.582 --> 02:37.517
for the squad to go to Vegas,
and you give us each $5,000.

02:37.518 --> 02:39.119
No, I see no value in that.

02:39.120 --> 02:41.287
But nine coworkers forced to
riddle their way free

02:41.288 --> 02:42.622
from a locked room...

02:42.623 --> 02:46.826
I would spend my $5,000 to buy
backstage passes to Britney,

02:46.827 --> 02:49.496
and then I'd ask her
one question:

02:49.497 --> 02:51.296
You think you're a better
dancer than me?

02:51.332 --> 02:52.899
We are not going to Las Vegas.

02:52.900 --> 02:55.702
We're going to Long Island City
and we will bond meaningfully,

02:55.703 --> 02:57.103
and that is a direct order.

02:57.104 --> 02:58.538
I'll see you at 8:00 tonight.

02:58.539 --> 02:59.873
Tonight?

02:59.874 --> 03:01.141
Um...

03:01.142 --> 03:02.808
Okay, great.

03:02.843 --> 03:04.310
Jake!
Jakester!

03:04.311 --> 03:05.845
Remember when I did not
email you about

03:05.846 --> 03:07.680
Captain Holt's "Escape the Room"
thing tonight?

03:07.681 --> 03:09.182
No, and I can't go.

03:09.183 --> 03:11.351
Amy and I are going to
my mom's house for my birthday.

03:11.352 --> 03:13.485
Adults don't care about
their birthdays.

03:13.521 --> 03:15.087
You came to work last year
on a horse.

03:15.122 --> 03:16.922
Man, forget you.
Where's Charles?

03:16.957 --> 03:18.390
On a stakeout
with Rosa and Terry.

03:18.425 --> 03:19.459
Police work?

03:19.460 --> 03:21.326
What a waste of time.
[groans]

03:21.362 --> 03:25.031
So no Jake, no Amy, no Charles,
no Rosa, no Terry.

03:25.032 --> 03:26.666
That leaves me with...

03:26.667 --> 03:28.401
Aah.
Ooh!

03:28.402 --> 03:30.370
- Aah.
- Aah.

03:30.371 --> 03:32.204
Oh, dear God.

03:32.239 --> 03:35.707
Okay, this is the block
our boy Tommy Tran does his drops.

03:35.743 --> 03:39.312
Before we do anything else,
are your body cams turned on?

03:39.313 --> 03:41.114
Why are you so obsessed
with these things?

03:41.115 --> 03:43.015
It's like your stupid babies
all over again.

03:43.050 --> 03:44.817
My babies are not stupid.

03:44.818 --> 03:46.753
Cagney can write a lowercase L.

03:46.754 --> 03:48.020
It's just a line, right?

03:48.055 --> 03:49.556
[groans]

03:49.557 --> 03:52.758
Look, I worked hard to get us
included in that pilot program.

03:52.793 --> 03:54.394
Body cams are important,

03:54.395 --> 03:56.563
and I need these field tests
to go well.

03:56.564 --> 03:58.731
I'm gonna go take my position.

03:58.732 --> 04:00.866
"Just a straight line." Come on!

04:00.901 --> 04:03.168
Unique New York.
Unique New York.

04:03.204 --> 04:05.071
Unique New York.

04:05.072 --> 04:07.367
I took a Toastmasters class
to prepare for tonight.

04:07.374 --> 04:08.675
Seriously, it's gonna be fine.

04:08.676 --> 04:10.243
We're just gonna have
some dinner, eat dessert,

04:10.244 --> 04:11.744
play charades,
and then talk for half an hour

04:11.745 --> 04:13.145
about which of her friends
are sick.

04:13.147 --> 04:14.447
We're gonna play charades?
[doorbell rings]

04:14.448 --> 04:16.783
You wait until t-minus
two seconds to tell me that?

04:16.784 --> 04:18.517
Okay.
Movie. Book.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.786
What's the thing for song?
I don't know the thing for song.

04:20.821 --> 04:21.820
[alarm beeping]

04:21.822 --> 04:24.023
Hi, birthday boy.

04:24.024 --> 04:25.057
Hi.

04:25.092 --> 04:26.525
Mom, is something on fire?

04:26.560 --> 04:28.627
- Yeah.
- Okay.

04:28.662 --> 04:31.931
You must be Amy.

04:31.932 --> 04:33.266
Let me take you in.

04:33.267 --> 04:35.401
Okay.

04:35.402 --> 04:38.303
I'll just take in this gorgeous
front door of yours.

04:38.339 --> 04:40.405
- Mom, seriously, the fire?
- It's fine.

04:40.441 --> 04:41.941
Things don't burn down
like they used to.

04:41.942 --> 04:43.942
I'm just gonna put it out.

04:43.978 --> 04:46.679
Well, you know, it's good
enough for Diane Keaton.

04:46.680 --> 04:47.947
It's good enough for me.

04:47.948 --> 04:49.015
I love her.

04:49.016 --> 04:51.551
I mean, she's no Jane Seymour.

04:51.552 --> 04:53.553
Where is Jane Seymour
now, anyway?

04:53.554 --> 04:56.055
She makes jewelry,
and it's beautiful.

04:56.056 --> 04:59.125
I just bought two brooches for
the lesbians across the street.

04:59.126 --> 05:00.260
Mom, I keep telling you,

05:00.261 --> 05:01.694
if you don't rein it in
a little bit,

05:01.695 --> 05:02.961
you're gonna scare them off.

05:02.997 --> 05:06.065
Well, that's what you said
about Carla, and I ignored it,

05:06.066 --> 05:07.899
and now I have a friend
with one arm.

05:07.935 --> 05:09.501
I stand corrected.
[doorbell rings]

05:09.536 --> 05:11.904
Oh, must be
your birthday surprise.

05:11.905 --> 05:13.339
You got the '86 Mets?

05:13.340 --> 05:15.708
Be warned, a lot of them
turned out to be drug addicts,

05:15.709 --> 05:17.509
so this could be a bummer.

05:17.544 --> 05:18.543
You ready?

05:20.781 --> 05:22.347
Hey, buddy.

05:22.383 --> 05:24.617
Happy birthday.

05:24.618 --> 05:26.885
Dad?
What are you doing here?

05:26.920 --> 05:29.322
I wanted to surprise you.

05:29.323 --> 05:33.192
Yeah, well I am surprised
that you know it's my birthday.

05:33.193 --> 05:35.928
Actually, Jake...

05:35.929 --> 05:37.964
your father and I are, uh,

05:37.965 --> 05:39.765
seeing each other again.

05:39.800 --> 05:41.567
Oh!

05:41.568 --> 05:44.804
Wow, that's...
that's so interesting.

05:44.805 --> 05:45.905
[pop]

05:45.906 --> 05:47.506
Oh...

05:50.230 --> 05:51.791
I know this isn't the best time,

05:51.792 --> 05:53.623
but we are in
your childhood bedroom,

05:53.624 --> 05:55.758
and I do have one question:

05:55.759 --> 05:57.894
did you have a nose ring
in high school?

05:57.895 --> 06:00.630
Yes. Until it got infected
and I almost went blind.

06:00.631 --> 06:01.630
Don't tell anyone.

06:01.665 --> 06:04.400
Cool. It's our secret.

06:04.401 --> 06:07.203
Just gonna check my email
up high.

06:07.204 --> 06:08.871
No new messages.

06:08.872 --> 06:10.606
Amy, can we focus?

06:10.607 --> 06:12.975
What is going on here?
Why is my dad dating my mom?

06:12.976 --> 06:14.143
What does he want?

06:14.144 --> 06:16.579
Money, but she's a public school
art teacher.

06:16.580 --> 06:18.514
That doesn't make any sense.
[snaps]

06:18.515 --> 06:20.716
Maybe that son of a bitch
wants his picture drawn!

06:20.717 --> 06:22.785
Jake, Karen is a grown woman

06:22.786 --> 06:24.754
with a pretty respectable
credit score.

06:24.755 --> 06:26.189
I'm sure she knows
what she's doing.

06:26.190 --> 06:27.490
Amy, I know that you
have a binder,

06:27.491 --> 06:28.658
but you don't know her
like I do.

06:28.659 --> 06:30.526
She's too trusting
for her own good.

06:30.527 --> 06:32.694
She's fallen for more
Nigerian scams than Scully.

06:32.729 --> 06:35.030
She's fallen
for 20 Nigerian scams?

06:35.065 --> 06:36.332
20?

06:36.333 --> 06:37.867
That's insane.

06:37.868 --> 06:40.336
No, she's fallen for 2.
Scully's fallen for 20?

06:40.337 --> 06:41.337
[scoffing] Yeah.

06:41.338 --> 06:42.772
Look, all right, you know what?

06:42.773 --> 06:44.073
This is fine.

06:44.074 --> 06:45.675
It's just the same
that it's always been.

06:45.676 --> 06:47.043
I have to protect her.

06:47.044 --> 06:48.311
I'm gonna go down there,

06:48.312 --> 06:50.179
and I'm going to express
my concerns to her

06:50.180 --> 06:52.248
in a calm, rational manner.

06:52.249 --> 06:53.983
[yelling]
What are you doing, Mom?

06:53.984 --> 06:55.417
He's evil!

06:55.452 --> 06:58.320
[gravelly voice] I'm glad
we got these sweet cams.

06:58.355 --> 06:59.487
What is happening
with your voice?

06:59.523 --> 07:01.324
This is Body Cam Charles.

07:01.325 --> 07:02.859
I got to sound badass

07:02.860 --> 07:05.261
in case anybody watches
the footage, capisce?

07:05.262 --> 07:06.294
[shrilly] Aah!

07:06.330 --> 07:08.697
Oh, I just spilled soup
on the cam!

07:08.732 --> 07:10.465
Why do you have soup
on a stakeout?

07:10.500 --> 07:12.335
Oh, no.
Crap!

07:12.336 --> 07:13.836
Oh, it's not turning back on.

07:13.837 --> 07:15.137
Do you think Sarge
is gonna be mad

07:15.138 --> 07:16.805
that I spilled "fuh" on the cam?

07:16.840 --> 07:18.174
He definitely will
if you say <i>pho</i> like that

07:18.175 --> 07:19.241
when you tell him.

07:19.276 --> 07:20.443
I'm not gonna mispronounce it.

07:20.444 --> 07:21.543
Not while you're rolling.

07:21.578 --> 07:22.744
Go get yourself cleaned up!

07:22.779 --> 07:23.778
[groans]

07:25.182 --> 07:26.581
- <i>See anything, Sarge?</i>
- Not yet.

07:26.617 --> 07:28.117
Don't know why
I didn't go undercover

07:28.118 --> 07:29.585
as someone wearing a scarf.

07:29.586 --> 07:31.888
Terry hates windchill.

07:31.889 --> 07:33.488
Wait, here's our guy.

07:33.523 --> 07:35.056
Got him.

07:35.092 --> 07:38.127
Crap!
I think he made me.

07:38.128 --> 07:39.762
He's headed toward
the restaurant!

07:39.763 --> 07:41.464
<i>You follow.
I'll cover the back alley!</i>

07:41.465 --> 07:44.467
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

07:44.468 --> 07:46.167
[tires squeal] [horn honks]

07:49.056 --> 07:50.372
Someone's in here!

07:53.043 --> 07:54.377
[grunts] Uhh!

07:54.378 --> 07:55.678
Ah!

07:55.679 --> 07:57.679
- Rosa?
- Charles.

07:58.916 --> 08:00.715
You're completely naked.

08:02.986 --> 08:04.586
You have the right
to remain silent.

08:04.621 --> 08:06.221
You have the right
to an attorney.

08:07.391 --> 08:08.858
[sighs]

08:08.859 --> 08:10.525
Where is everyone, Gina?

08:10.560 --> 08:12.862
Perhaps that's
tonight's first puzzle.

08:12.863 --> 08:14.663
I forgot to send
the invitations.

08:14.698 --> 08:16.899
But I was able to rally
the best and brightest

08:16.900 --> 08:18.366
of those available.

08:20.037 --> 08:21.036
Oh, dear God.

08:21.038 --> 08:22.238
Sorry we're late.

08:22.239 --> 08:23.973
Turns out the front door
was a push, not a pull.

08:23.974 --> 08:25.273
Well, maybe we should
just reschedule.

08:25.309 --> 08:26.309
[doors slam]

08:26.310 --> 08:28.110
[alarm sounding]

08:28.111 --> 08:30.546
<i>You have three hours
to find the four keys</i>

08:30.547 --> 08:32.181
<i>that will prevent the apocalypse</i>

08:32.182 --> 08:33.581
<i>and release you from this room.</i>

08:33.616 --> 08:35.650
<i>Your time starts now.</i>

08:35.652 --> 08:37.919
Well, this is
a sobering reality.

08:39.456 --> 08:42.224
Okay, I got your favorite cake:

08:42.225 --> 08:44.593
- blue.
- I'm not hungry.

08:44.594 --> 08:47.196
It's a figure of speech.
Obviously, I'll have some.

08:47.197 --> 08:49.532
You know,
I don't think our guest Amy

08:49.533 --> 08:52.001
really wants to
talk about this, Jake.

08:52.002 --> 08:53.568
Can we just move on?

08:53.603 --> 08:55.304
Yes.
Maybe we could talk about

08:55.305 --> 08:58.507
someone we all admire:
President Jimmy Carter.

08:58.508 --> 09:00.109
When I think of the great...

09:00.110 --> 09:02.478
So how serious is it, Hmm?

09:02.479 --> 09:03.545
Have you guys kissed?

09:03.580 --> 09:04.880
Has he stayed the night?

09:04.881 --> 09:07.116
Has he brought you a chocolate
orange from the airport?

09:07.117 --> 09:08.583
'Cause that's his big move.

09:08.618 --> 09:10.319
Jake, your mother
and I have been seeing each other

09:10.320 --> 09:11.319
for three months.

09:11.321 --> 09:12.321
Oh, you know what?

09:12.322 --> 09:14.122
I oughta throw up in your face.

09:14.157 --> 09:18.693
I know that you're angry,
but when I was here last year,

09:18.729 --> 09:21.464
you really showed me
what a selfish jerk I was.

09:21.465 --> 09:24.332
You're the reason
that all of this is happening.

09:24.368 --> 09:26.068
Yeah, but I didn't want this.

09:26.069 --> 09:29.404
I just wanted you to text me
Mb dad joke every six months.

09:29.439 --> 09:30.805
I can do that.
Just give me your number.

09:30.841 --> 09:32.375
You didn't save my number?

09:32.376 --> 09:33.842
Now, Jake, look.

09:33.877 --> 09:36.145
I know every mistake
your father has made,

09:36.146 --> 09:38.881
and he says
they're all in the past.

09:38.882 --> 09:41.367
Now just blow out your candles.

09:42.219 --> 09:43.219
Okay, great.

09:43.220 --> 09:44.320
Great idea, Mom.

09:44.321 --> 09:47.189
I'll blow out
my birthday candles.

09:47.190 --> 09:49.592
[inhales deeply]

09:49.593 --> 09:51.494
[blows]

09:51.495 --> 09:54.363
[whispering]
I wished that you would leave.

09:54.364 --> 09:55.898
Damn it, I shouldn't have
said it out loud.

09:55.899 --> 09:56.898
Now it won't come true.

09:56.900 --> 10:01.237
Okay, we have maps,
a pantry, beds, a desk.

10:01.238 --> 10:02.538
Where should we begin?

10:02.539 --> 10:04.140
Do you have any experience
with puzzles?

10:04.141 --> 10:05.141
Yes.

10:05.142 --> 10:06.341
I've never solved one.

10:06.376 --> 10:08.711
This says we have
three questions.

10:08.712 --> 10:10.045
- No.
- Uh-oh.

10:10.080 --> 10:11.680
- How do we get outta here?
- <i>Can't tell you.</i>

10:11.681 --> 10:12.681
- Really?
-<i> Yes.</i>

10:12.682 --> 10:14.817
That's enough!

10:14.818 --> 10:16.085
Sorry about that.

10:16.086 --> 10:17.620
Can we please have
our questions back?

10:17.621 --> 10:18.621
<i>No.</i>

10:18.622 --> 10:19.688
<i>And that's three.</i>

10:19.689 --> 10:21.257
<i>You're done.</i>

10:21.258 --> 10:24.125
Oh, Captain, how could you?

10:25.228 --> 10:26.796
Hey.

10:26.797 --> 10:28.364
You didn't come back down.

10:28.365 --> 10:30.633
I had to talk to your parents
for, like, an hour,

10:30.634 --> 10:32.435
and I ran out of stuff
from the binder,

10:32.436 --> 10:34.770
and then I did something
really weird.

10:34.771 --> 10:38.974
♪ The itsy-bitsy spider
went up the water spout ♪

10:38.975 --> 10:40.342
♪ Down came... ♪

10:40.343 --> 10:43.678
So... do you know where
the nearest train station is?

10:43.713 --> 10:47.249
I know it sucks that I did that,
but think about how I feel.

10:47.250 --> 10:49.485
My stupid parents
are borking each other.

10:49.486 --> 10:51.487
And my mom thinks she knows
all the worst things

10:51.488 --> 10:53.422
that my dad did,
but she has no idea.

10:53.423 --> 10:55.157
She doesn't even know
that he cheated on her

10:55.158 --> 10:57.358
with her best friend,
Sheila Bodden.

10:57.394 --> 10:58.394
Oh, my God.

10:58.395 --> 10:59.562
Yeah, I saw them.

